title: Rescue teams in desperate search for survivors after deadly quake in Morocco
description: The death toll Saturday had passed 1,300 and international search and rescue teams were still waiting on a green light from local authorities.

title: At G-20, Biden announces ambitious corridor connecting India, Europe
description: Senior administration officials view the corridor as a way to open up the flow of both energy and digital information, as well as have Israel work with historic adversaries like Saudi Arabia.

title: Deepening rift among Republicans threatens future of Ukraine aid
description: The GOP’s right flank is making it tough for moderate Republicans to convince constituents that standing with Ukraine is consistent with conservative values.

title: U.K. police recapture escaped prisoner after a nationwide manhunt
description: Daniel Abed Khalife, a terrorism suspect whose sensational escape from a London prison launched a four-day manhunt, has been found and arrested, police said.

title: Map shows Morocco earthquake’s devastating impact on populated areas
description: Morocco’s earthquake struck the province of Al Haouz, and was felt in Marrakesh, as well as Casablanca, Rabat, Fez, and other cities.

title: In photos: Hundreds dead after powerful quake rocks Morocco
description: A deadly 6.8-magnitude earthquake hit near the historic Moroccan city of Marrakesh late Friday night. It was also felt in Casablanca, Rabat and other cities.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky says no compromise with ‘liar’ Putin
description: President Volodymyr Zelensky told CNN he wouldn’t trust a deal with President Vladimir Putin, citing the death of Putin’s former ally, Yevgeniy Prigozhin.

title: At least 296 dead as powerful earthquake hits Morocco
description: The 6.8-magnitude earthquake struck at 11:11 p.m. on Friday, about 44 miles southeast of Marrakesh.
